Simple QR Code Generator
This is a minimalistic Python mini-project that generates a QR code for a given URL using the qrcode library. The generated QR code is saved as an image file.
Requirements
Python 3.x
qrcode library
Installation
You can install the required library using the following command:
pip install qrcode[pil]
Usage
Clone the repository or download the source code.
git clone https://github.com/your-username/simple-qrcode-generator.git
cd simple-qrcode-generator
Modify the generate_qrcode.py file to include the desired URL.
import qrcode as qr

url = "https://github.com/gunna-rahul"
img = qr.make(url)
img.save("gunnarahul_github.png")
print(f"QR code for {url} generated and saved as gunnarahul_github.png.")
Run the script:
python generate_qrcode.py
The generated QR code image will be saved in the same directory as gunnarahul_github.png.
Customize
You can customize the script by changing the value of the url variable in the generate_qrcode.py file. Feel free to modify the script to accept user input or generate QR codes for different URLs.
